{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/FactoryKit\/documentation\/FactoryKit"]]},"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Advanced Topics","identifiers":["doc:\/\/FactoryKit\/documentation\/FactoryKit\/Design","doc:\/\/FactoryKit\/documentation\/FactoryKit\/Modifiers","doc:\/\/FactoryKit\/documentation\/FactoryKit\/Modules","doc:\/\/FactoryKit\/documentation\/FactoryKit\/Cycle","doc:\/\/FactoryKit\/documentation\/FactoryKit\/Optionals","doc:\/\/FactoryKit\/documentation\/FactoryKit\/Tags"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Advanced-Topics"}],"kind":"article","sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Factory can inject more than service classes and structs."}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/factorykit\/functional"]}],"metadata":{"role":"article","modules":[{"name":"FactoryKit"}],"title":"Functional Injection","roleHeading":"Article"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Functional Injection is a powerful tool that can, in many cases, eliminate the need for defining protocols, implementations, and the various stubs and mocks one needs when doing traditional Protocol-Oriented-Programing.","type":"text"}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Example","text":"Example","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Consider the following typealias and Factory."}]},{"code":["typealias AccountProviding = () async throws -> [Account]","","extension Container {","    var accountProvider: Factory<AccountProviding> {","        self {{ try await Network.get(path: \"\/accounts\") }}","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note the double braces. In this example our factory closure is returning a closure, not a class or struct."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Now, here’s the view model that uses it.","type":"text"}]},{"code":["class AccountViewModel: ObservableObject {","    @Injected(\\.accountProvider) var accountProvider","    @Published var accounts: [Account] = []","    @MainActor func load() async {","        do {","            accounts = try await accountProvider()","        } catch {","            print(error)","        }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Testing","text":"Testing","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Now consider how easy it is to write a test with mock accounts…"}]},{"code":["func testAllAccounts() async {","    Container.shared.accountProvider.register {{ Account.mockAccounts }}","    do {","        let viewModel = AccountViewModel()","        try await viewModel.load()","        XCTAssert(viewModel.accounts.count == 5)","    } catch {","        XCTFail(\"Account load failed\")","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Or test edge cases like no accounts found."}]},{"code":["func testEmptyAccounts() async {","    Container.shared.accountProvider.register {{ [] }}","    ...","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Or test specific error cases."}]},{"code":["func testErrorLoadingAccounts() async {","    Container.shared.accountProvider.register {{ throw APIError.network }}","    ...","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Here’s an article that goes into the technique in more detail: "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/betterprogramming.pub\/factory-and-functional-dependency-injection-2d0a38042d05","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/FactoryKit\/documentation\/FactoryKit\/Functional"},"references":{"doc://FactoryKit/documentation/FactoryKit/Modules":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Using Factory in a project with multiple modules."}],"type":"topic","title":"Modular Development","url":"\/documentation\/factorykit\/modules","role":"article","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/FactoryKit\/documentation\/FactoryKit\/Modules"},"https://betterprogramming.pub/factory-and-functional-dependency-injection-2d0a38042d05":{"title":"Factory and Functional Dependency Injection","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Factory and Functional Dependency Injection"}],"url":"https:\/\/betterprogramming.pub\/factory-and-functional-dependency-injection-2d0a38042d05","identifier":"https:\/\/betterprogramming.pub\/factory-and-functional-dependency-injection-2d0a38042d05","type":"link"},"doc://FactoryKit/documentation/FactoryKit":{"kind":"symbol","role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/factorykit","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A modern approach to Container-Based Dependency Injection for Swift and SwiftUI."}],"title":"FactoryKit","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/FactoryKit\/documentation\/FactoryKit"},"doc://FactoryKit/documentation/FactoryKit/Cycle":{"role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/FactoryKit\/documentation\/FactoryKit\/Cycle","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"What’s a resolution cycle, and why should we care?"}],"kind":"article","type":"topic","title":"Resolution Cycles","url":"\/documentation\/factorykit\/cycle"},"doc://FactoryKit/documentation/FactoryKit/Design":{"url":"\/documentation\/factorykit\/design","type":"topic","role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/FactoryKit\/documentation\/FactoryKit\/Design","kind":"article","title":"Designing Factory","abstract":[{"text":"Rationale behind the design decisions made in Factory 1.0 and 2.0","type":"text"}]},"doc://FactoryKit/documentation/FactoryKit/Modifiers":{"kind":"article","title":"Factory Modifiers","type":"topic","role":"article","url":"\/documentation\/factorykit\/modifiers","identifier":"doc:\/\/FactoryKit\/documentation\/FactoryKit\/Modifiers","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Considerations when defining and redefining a Factory’s behavior."}]},"doc://FactoryKit/documentation/FactoryKit/Tags":{"abstract":[{"text":"Obtaining a list of dependencies of a given type.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","title":"Tags","url":"\/documentation\/factorykit\/tags","role":"article","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/FactoryKit\/documentation\/FactoryKit\/Tags"},"doc://FactoryKit/documentation/FactoryKit/Optionals":{"kind":"article","title":"Optionals and Dynamic Registration","type":"topic","role":"article","url":"\/documentation\/factorykit\/optionals","identifier":"doc:\/\/FactoryKit\/documentation\/FactoryKit\/Optionals","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"With Factory registrations can be performed at any time."}]}}}